	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">Who built Fasilides Castle?</h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 150%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		It was built by Emperor Fasiladas who, after growing bored with the migratory semi-nomadic lifestyle of his predecessors, decided to make a statement by building a grandiose palace complex - one of the most magnificent structures of its time.
	</p>
	<video style="margin-left:230px;" width="70%"controls>
		<source src="image/gonder.mp4" type="video/mp4">

		</video><br>
	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">When was Fasilides castle built?</h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 157%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		Fasil Castle was constructed with a medieval exterior appearance in 1632-1667 out of stone and timber materials as a private residence for Emperor Fasiledes. Fasil Castle is still in use today as a museum, although public access is only allowed on the first floor.
	</p>
